The Magic of Atlantis is an anthology of fantasy short stories, edited by Lin Carter. It was first published in paperback by Lancer Books in 1970.
The book collects seven fantasy tales by various authors set on the fictional lost continent of Atlantis, with an afterword by Carter.

== Contents ==
"The Death of Malygris" (Clark Ashton Smith)
"The Eye of Tandyla" (L. Sprague de Camp)
"The Mirrors of Tuzun Thune" (Robert E. Howard)
"The Heart of Atlantan" (Nictzin Dyalhis)
"The Vengeance of Ulios" (Edmond Hamilton)
"The Seal of Zaon Sathla" (Lin Carter)
"The Spawn of Dagon" (Henry Kuttner)
"Beyond the Pillars of Hercules" (afterword) (Lin Carter)